00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:11,306
Gotta keep moving.

514
00:31:36,519 --> 00:31:39,239
Please don't hurt me...
please don't hurt me.

515
00:31:39,278 --> 00:31:40,802
Please don't hurt me!

516
00:31:41,110 --> 00:31:42,519
Please don't hurt me...

517
00:31:42,866 --> 00:31:43,893
Mimi?

518
00:31:47,129 --> 00:31:50,061
- It's Gail and Johnston Green, honey.
You're safe.  - Oh, thanks God!

519
00:31:50,264 --> 00:31:51,972
Come on, baby,
let's get out of here.

520
00:31:52,300 --> 00:31:53,342
Come on.

521
00:32:01,521 --> 00:32:02,872
Those are hideous.

522
00:32:02,873 --> 00:32:04,878
Are those the sheets
from your old apartment?

523
00:32:05,225 --> 00:32:07,541
Because you can't expect
anyone to sleep on those.

524
00:32:07,999 --> 00:32:10,970
If anyone asks, we'll pretend
someone else donated them.

525
00:32:20,211 --> 00:32:21,233
Your dress.

526
00:32:23,818 --> 00:32:25,439
Guess I shouldn't be seeing this, huh?

527
00:32:26,905 --> 00:32:29,027
The day's sort of come and gone, so...

528
00:32:30,955 --> 00:32:32,055
It'll come again.

529
00:32:32,769 --> 00:32:33,772
You think?

530
00:32:35,548 --> 00:32:36,667
I do.

531
00:32:38,133 --> 00:32:40,159
I tell you what, I've got
a pack of Ramen noodles

532
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,760
with your name on it,
what do you say?

533
00:32:42,184 --> 00:32:45,078
Great. I'll deliver this to the shelter
and come back and wash up.

534
00:32:45,637 --> 00:32:47,046
Roger, wait.

535
00:32:48,723 --> 00:32:50,093
I'll come with you.

536
00:33:06,666 --> 00:33:08,325
It's Mom and Dad, honey!

537
00:33:08,961 --> 00:33:10,813
Stanley, you all right, sweetheart?

538
00:33:11,738 --> 00:33:13,841
You need to go get in the truck
and get warm, pal.

539
00:33:13,842 --> 00:33:15,520
- Where's Mimi?
- I'm right here.

540
00:33:15,579 --> 00:33:16,891
Stanley, I'm right here.

541
00:33:19,572 --> 00:33:21,482
Wake up. Wake up!

542
00:33:22,331 --> 00:33:23,527
Wake up, Jake.

543
00:33:23,932 --> 00:33:24,935
Wake up.

544
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:26,340
Wake up. Oh, thank God.

545
00:33:26,341 --> 00:33:27,690
We're gonna help you, honey.

546
00:33:29,909 --> 00:33:31,240
We saw the storm coming

547
00:33:31,549 --> 00:33:33,710
and we started to worry
when you hadn't come back.

548
00:33:33,711 --> 00:33:34,809
Sweetheart...

549
00:33:37,549 --> 00:33:38,398
Honey,

550
00:33:38,399 --> 00:33:40,616
we're not gonna be able
to get this truck off of him.

551
00:33:40,617 --> 00:33:42,506
I need you to take
these guys back to town

552
00:33:42,507 --> 00:33:44,015
and get me some help out here.

553
00:33:44,016 --> 00:33:46,673
You signal when you're coming back
so I know it's you, all right?

554
00:33:46,674 --> 00:33:49,084
- I'll flash the lights.
- All right, go, go, go!

555
00:33:51,262 --> 00:33:52,690
Jake, look at me, son.

556
00:33:52,691 --> 00:33:53,693
Lookie here.

557
00:33:54,001 --> 00:33:56,220
You're gonna make it, son...
I know you.

558
00:33:57,204 --> 00:33:59,905
I know what you're made of.
You're gonna be all right.

559
00:34:00,445 --> 00:34:03,049
You're gonna make it.
Stay with me now.

560
00:34:16,570 --> 00:34:19,194
Robert, please,
the kids are sleeping.

561
00:34:19,753 --> 00:34:22,319
- I'm sorry.
- What on earth are you doing?

562
00:34:22,662 --> 00:34:24,186
Oh, I'm sorry.

563
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:38,811
Jake, you'll be home real soon,

564
00:34:39,217 --> 00:34:41,300
but you got to stay
with me now. Come on.

565
00:34:43,663 --> 00:34:45,506
Leave me here.
Leave me alone.

566
00:34:45,776 --> 00:34:47,435
Now, I'm not going anywhere.

567
00:34:47,995 --> 00:34:49,557
But you got to hang on.

568
00:34:49,866 --> 00:34:51,757
Now, they'll be here soon, son.

569
00:34:53,802 --> 00:34:54,814
Dad...

570
00:34:55,431 --> 00:34:56,676
I'm sorry.

571
00:34:57,521 --> 00:34:59,643
Oh, son, you got nothing
to be sorry about.

572
00:35:04,467 --> 00:35:06,415
Open your eyes, Jake.
Come on, now.

573
00:35:07,264 --> 00:35:09,406
Look at me.
Look at me, Jake.

574
00:35:11,682 --> 00:35:13,168
I can see her.

575
00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:16,351
See who?

576
00:35:17,952 --> 00:35:19,322
The girl.

577
00:35:21,617 --> 00:35:23,257
What... girl?

578
00:35:23,258 --> 00:35:24,994
Jake, I think you're hallucinating, son.

579
00:35:24,995 --> 00:35:26,017
No, listen to me.

580
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:30,126
When I was in Iraq...

581
00:35:32,538 --> 00:35:34,139
... there was a girl.

582
00:35:36,474 --> 00:35:38,191
She couldn't have been more than...

583
00:35:38,882 --> 00:35:40,039
10 or 12...

584
00:35:40,946 --> 00:35:42,297
Don't talk now, son.

585
00:35:42,489 --> 00:35:43,512
You save your energy.

586
00:35:43,513 --> 00:35:45,133
We'll talk when we get... home.

587
00:35:46,445 --> 00:35:47,949
I killed her, Dad.

588
00:35:53,834 --> 00:35:55,531
I killed a little girl.

589
00:36:15,576 --> 00:36:16,907
Hurry up!

590
00:36:29,948 --> 00:36:31,434
Open your eyes, Jake.

591
00:36:31,435 --> 00:36:32,804
Open your eyes.

592
00:36:34,096 --> 00:36:35,870
All right, everyone on three...

593
00:36:35,871 --> 00:36:36,874
One,

594
00:36:37,202 --> 00:36:38,687
two, three!

595
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:45,130
All right, he's free.

596
00:36:45,632 --> 00:36:46,924
Let's get the board in here.

597
00:36:47,928 --> 00:36:49,761
One, two, three.

598
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:01,703
You were right.

599
00:37:01,704 --> 00:37:04,635
I need to get my family
as far away from me as possible.

600
00:37:05,542 --> 00:37:07,046
I've been thinking, and...

601
00:37:07,837 --> 00:37:09,497
There's no other choice.

602
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:12,757
You're doing the right thing.

603
00:37:14,204 --> 00:37:15,284
Listen.

604
00:37:17,214 --> 00:37:18,603
After they're safe,

605
00:37:19,124 --> 00:37:20,976
you and me need
to get back in the field.

606
00:37:21,477 --> 00:37:23,406
That's half our team gone, Sarah,

607
00:37:23,407 --> 00:37:25,621
and whoever did that
did it for a reason.

608
00:37:28,611 --> 00:37:30,290
How are you gonna tell Darcy?

609
00:37:33,356 --> 00:37:35,151
I'll tell her after I've moved them.

610
00:37:36,385 --> 00:37:39,048
She'll never agree if she knows
I won't be staying with them.

611
00:37:49,775 --> 00:37:51,704
He's better off here
than the med center.

612
00:37:51,955 --> 00:37:55,080
We're still on emergency power,
and it's... it's warmer here.

613
00:37:56,643 --> 00:37:57,974
Here, honey.

614
00:37:58,611 --> 00:37:59,861
What about his injuries?

615
00:37:59,862 --> 00:38:01,775
Well, the cut on his head
isn't very deep,

616
00:38:01,776 --> 00:38:03,912
and neither one
of his legs are broken.

617
00:38:04,645 --> 00:38:05,860
He's very lucky.

618
00:38:05,861 --> 00:38:07,172
I'm freezing.

619
00:38:07,597 --> 00:38:09,410
I'm gonna go get you
some more blankets.

620
00:38:09,892 --> 00:38:11,416
You're still hypothermic.

621
00:38:11,417 --> 00:38:14,426
It's just gonna take a few hours
for your body to stabilize.

622
00:38:16,123 --> 00:38:18,265
- Can we have a minute?
- Oh, sure.

623
00:38:33,699 --> 00:38:34,992
Dad...

624
00:38:39,641 --> 00:38:41,185
What I told you out there...

625
00:38:44,079 --> 00:38:45,661
please forget it.

626
00:38:47,359 --> 00:38:48,516
Please.

627
00:38:52,278 --> 00:38:53,706
Afraid I can't do that.

628
00:39:06,069 --> 00:39:08,423
I've seen a lot of things
in my time, Jake.

629
00:39:10,777 --> 00:39:11,992
I've been to war.

630
00:39:13,304 --> 00:39:16,680
I know what war can do.
I know what men can do... Terrible...

631
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:19,575
... terrible things.

632
00:39:22,482 --> 00:39:23,833
I know what I did.

633
00:39:26,495 --> 00:39:28,000
You can talk to me.

634
00:39:53,466 --> 00:39:54,874
When you're ready, son.

635
00:39:58,213 --> 00:39:59,428
When you're ready.

636
00:40:17,467 --> 00:40:18,836
You okay?

637
00:40:27,132 --> 00:40:28,405
How's the sprain?

638
00:40:29,949 --> 00:40:32,978
I think it'd be better with painkillers,
but I'm not gonna complain.

639
00:40:33,884 --> 00:40:37,006
You know, for a while there, I didn't
think I'd ever feel anything again.

640
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:41,404
When I was out there,

641
00:40:41,925 --> 00:40:43,257
just for a moment,

642
00:40:44,318 --> 00:40:46,093
I didn't think
I was gonna make it.

643
00:40:47,136 --> 00:40:49,799
And I stopped... to rest.

644
00:40:50,686 --> 00:40:53,175
And then I just didn't
even want to move.

645
00:40:56,763 --> 00:40:57,940
But you did.

646
00:40:59,445 --> 00:41:00,757
You did make it.

647
00:41:02,223 --> 00:41:03,786
And I knew you would.

648
00:41:10,441 --> 00:41:12,313
Your lips are still cold.

649
00:41:14,608 --> 00:41:16,460
Maybe you can warm them.

650
00:41:21,052 --> 00:41:23,309
That's the worst line
I've ever heard.

651
00:41:23,830 --> 00:41:25,740
I know. I've got others.

652
00:41:26,975 --> 00:41:28,576
- Shut up.
- Okay.

653
00:41:39,405 --> 00:41:40,738
Tomorrow morning...

654
00:41:42,899 --> 00:41:43,973
we're leaving.

655
00:41:45,282 --> 00:41:47,110
We're leaving?
For... for where?

656
00:41:49,060 --> 00:41:50,258
I don't know yet.

657
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:52,492
You don't know?

658
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:59,444
Darcy, when I came
to get you in DC...

659
00:42:01,556 --> 00:42:03,223
I told you it wasn't safe,

660
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,446
but I couldn't tell you why.

661
00:42:10,978 --> 00:42:12,176
I'm going for a walk.

662
00:42:25,529 --> 00:42:27,336
I have something
in my possession.

663
00:42:29,550 --> 00:42:31,366
And there's people
out there that want it,

664
00:42:31,921 --> 00:42:34,094
that will stop at nothing to get it.

665
00:42:36,411 --> 00:42:38,011
And that puts you,
me and the kids

666
00:42:38,406 --> 00:42:39,532
in danger here.

667
00:42:45,686 --> 00:42:47,790
Okay, so th... then we go.

668
00:42:49,133 --> 00:42:50,338
<i>I trust you.</i>

669
00:42:56,047 --> 00:42:57,212
<i>Robert, do y...</i>

670
00:42:58,665 --> 00:42:59,732
Do you trust me?

671
00:43:02,725 --> 00:43:05,008
- You're late.
- You're impatient.

672
00:43:10,301 --> 00:43:11,792
Then listen to me.

673
00:43:12,671 --> 00:43:14,835
Okay, Sarah is not on our side.

674
00:43:15,299 --> 00:43:16,721
Now... whatever's...

675
00:43:17,224 --> 00:43:18,548
gone on between the two of you,

676
00:43:18,549 --> 00:43:20,869
I'm telling you, Robert,
she's not here to help us.

677
00:43:24,395 --> 00:43:25,877
Have you located the package?

678
00:43:26,588 --> 00:43:27,593
Soon.

679
00:43:29,036 --> 00:43:30,973
Hawkins is starting to put
the pieces together.

680
00:43:30,974 --> 00:43:33,502
- He needs to be eliminated.
- I know.

681
00:43:33,718 --> 00:43:36,623
We've already eliminated the other
three targets without incident.

682
00:43:36,624 --> 00:43:38,303
Why are you stalling on this one?

683
00:43:49,296 --> 00:43:51,064
Because this one is different.

